.TH CHWN 1 "2026" "The-JLC-Project" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
chwn \- change file owner and group
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B chwn
.I owner
.I group
.I file
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B chwn
changes the owner and group of
.IR file .
Both symbolic names (e.g.
.BR root ,
.BR wheel )
and numeric IDs are accepted.
.PP
Symbolic names are resolved via
.BR getpwnam (3)
and
.BR getgrnam (3).
Numeric strings fall back to
.BR atoi (3).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Wrong number of arguments.
.TP
.B 2
Unknown user or group name.
.TP
.B 3
.BR chown (2)
syscall failed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Change owner to root, group to wheel:
.EX
chwn root wheel /etc/myfile
.EE
.TP
Use numeric IDs:
.EX
chwn 0 0 /etc/myfile
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR chown (1),
.BR chgrp (1)
.SH AUTHORS
The-JLC-Project contributors.
